			        </item>
        <item>
			<title>Tim Bowling on Book Collecting and his book In the Suicide's Library</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://nigelbeale.libsyn.com/tim-bowling-on-book-collecting-and-his-book-in-the-suicide-s-library]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_IChG84ns88I/TLyIPFjKk-I/AAAAAAAAAuE/G2oZ_NkyOxs/s1600/101018+Bowling.JPG" alt="" height="302" width="341" /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: large;">Tim Bowling's collections of poetry include <em>Fathom, The Book Collector,</em> and <em>The Memory Orchard</em>. He has written three novels, including <em>The Bone Sharps</em> and <em>The Paperboy&rsquo;s Winter</em>. Twice shortlisted for the Governor General&rsquo;s Award for Poetry, Tim has won the Canadian Authors&rsquo; Association Award for Poetry and two Alberta Book Awards. In 2008, he was awarded a Guggenheim Fellowship. He lives in Edmonton, Alberta.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: large;">Tim was in Ottawa recently for Versefest. We met to talk about his book <a href="http://www.gaspereau.com/bookInfo.php?AID=0&amp;AISBN=9781554470891"><em>In the Suicide's Library</em></a>,&nbsp; an entertaining, fast-paced meditation ( yes, unusual) on modern life, the responsibilities of marriage and parenting, middle-age&nbsp; and books and book collecting. Topics covered include book collecting, coincidence, suicide, the spirit, passion and harmony of books, &nbsp;the use of hands, the line between bibliophiles and maniacs, the importance of physical books to the culture; we also cover writing about one&rsquo;s book collections; &nbsp;the sense of community among book collectors, the temptation of the material, possession, The Great Gatsby and green light, Las Vegas, &nbsp;the power of knowledge, the pros and cons of the Internet, Serendipity Books, &lsquo;shattering the groove,&rsquo; mid-life, change, parenthood,&nbsp; and investing life with meaning.</span></p>]]></description>
            <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[799c8edd536eea2b4be1d2f148c62b03]]></guid>
            <media:thumbnail url="http://assets.libsyn.com/item/1904560" />
