        <item>
			<title>Leah Gordon on the Alcuin Society's Awards for Excellence in Book Design in Canada</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://nigelbeale.libsyn.com/leah-gordon-on-the-alcuin-society-s-awards-for-excellence-in-book-design-in-canada]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nigelbeale/6900032019/" _fcksavedurl="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nigelbeale/6900032019/" title="Leah Gordon, Chair of the Awards Committee, Alcuin Society by Literary Tourist, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7182/6900032019_7ed0e82549.jpg" _fcksavedurl="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7182/6900032019_7ed0e82549.jpg" alt="Leah Gordon, Chair of the Awards Committee, Alcuin Society" height="404" width="277" /></a></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4"><span lang="EN-GB"><a _fcksavedurl="http://www.alcuinsociety.com/awards/" href="http://www.alcuinsociety.com/awards/">The Alcuin Society&rsquo;s Awards for Excellence in Book Design in Canada</a> have been recognizing achievement since 1981.</span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4"><span lang="EN-GB">As Marlene Chan put it in the preface to the 2009 winners&rsquo;catalogue, </span></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4"><span lang="EN-GB">&ldquo;The hallmark of the judging process in all of the Alcuin competitions is, and has always been, that each book is considered as a total entity. The discerning judges examine every aspect of each book, including the dust jacket, binding, endpapers, half-title page, copyright page, title page, page layout, typography, integration of illustrations, chapter openings, running heads, reproduction of illustrations, clarity of printing, choice of paper, footnotes and bibliographical references. The judges select books in eight categories to encourage the very best in Canadian design, only where they see exceptional merit.&rdquo;</span></span></p>
</blockquote>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4"><span lang="EN-GB">I met recently with Leah Gordon, Chair of the Book Design Committee, at her home in Vancouver to talk about the history and goals of the society &ndash; and, in particular, its Awards program; about some of the books the society has published over the years, and </span></span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4"><span lang="EN-GB"><span>about </span>how</span></span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4"><span lang="EN-GB">, in addition to the judging criteria cited above,&nbsp;<span></span> appropriateness and usefulness also factor into the judges&rsquo; decision making process.&nbsp; <span><br /></span></span></span></p>]]></description>
            <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[83284cd88254f88d583abb970c3a4c1c]]></guid>
            <media:thumbnail url="http://assets.libsyn.com/item/1857872" />
            <pubDate>Sun, 19 Feb 2012 12:21:16 +0000</pubDate>
            <itunes:explicit>no</itunes:explicit>
			<itunes:keywords>books,design,arts,canadian,book,society,awards,robert,collecting,reid,alcuin</itunes:keywords>

	<itunes:subtitle><![CDATA[
The Alcuin Society&rsquo;s Awards for Excellence in Book Design in Canada have been recognizing achievement since 1981.
As Marlene Chan put it in the preface to the 2009 winners&rsquo;catalogue, 

&ldquo;The hallmark of the judging process in all of the Alcuin competitions is, and has always been, that each book is considered as a total entity. The discerning judges examine every aspect of each book, including the dust jacket, binding, endpapers, half-title page, copyright page, title page, page layout, typography, integration of illustrations, chapter openings, running heads, reproduction of illustrations, clarity of printing, choice of paper, footnotes and bibliographical references. The judges select books in eight categories to encourage the very best in Canadian design, only where they see exceptional merit.&rdquo;

I met recently with Leah Gordon, Chair of the Book Design Committee, at her home in Vancouver to talk about the history and goals of the society &ndash; and, in particular, its Awards program; about some of the books the society has published over the years, and about how, in addition to the judging criteria cited above,&nbsp; appropriateness and usefulness also factor into the judges&rsquo; decision making process.&nbsp; ]]></itunes:subtitle>



            <itunes:duration>18:22</itunes:duration>
            <enclosure length="7711200" type="audio/mpeg" url="http://traffic.libsyn.com/nigelbeale/Leah_Gordon_56_R09_0002_3.mp3" />
			        </item>
        <item>
			<title>Interview with poet bill bissett</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://nigelbeale.libsyn.com/interview-with-poet-bill-bissett]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><a title="bill bissett by Literary Tourist, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nigelbeale/6884286425/" _fcksavedurl="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nigelbeale/6884286425/"><img alt="bill bissett" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7205/6884286425_8171085475.jpg" _fcksavedurl="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7205/6884286425_8171085475.jpg" height="369" width="276" /></a></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_bissett" _fcksavedurl="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_bissett">Monsieur Wikipedia</a> informs us that bill bissett was born in Halifax, Nova Scotia, attended Dalhousie University (1956) and the University of British Columbia (1963&ndash;1965), and dropped out of both because of a desire 'to live as a free agent, writer and painter unencumbered by any academic constraints.' He moved to Vancouver in 1958 and five years later set up <i>blew ointment magazine</i>. He later launched <a title="Blewointment press (page does not exist)" class="new" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Blewointment_press&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" _fcksavedurl="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Blewointment_press&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1">blewointment press</a>, which has published volumes by Cathy Ford, Maxine Gadd, bpNichol, Ken West, Lionel Kearns and D. A. Levy, and many others.&nbsp; bissett is currently based in Vancouver and Toronto.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4">Known for his 'unique orthography' , 4 incorporating visual elements into his printed poetry, and 4 performing "concrete sound" poetry using sound effects, chanting, and barefoot dancing, he is often associated with the Shamanistic in literature. He also paints, and produces audio recordings. His work 'often involves humour, a sense of wonder and sentimentality, and political commentary.'</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4">In 2006, <a href="http://www.harbourpublishing.com/title/RadiantDanseUvBeing" _fcksavedurl="http://www.harbourpublishing.com/title/RadiantDanseUvBeing">Harbour Publishing put out&nbsp; <i>radiant danse uv being</i></a>, a tribute to bissett with contributions from more than 80 writers, including Margaret Atwood, Leonard Cohen, Patrick Lane, Steve McCaffery, and P. K. Page; and Carl Peters has just published a book called <a href="http://talonbooks.com/books/textual-vishyuns" _fcksavedurl="http://talonbooks.com/books/textual-vishyuns"><i>textual vishyuns: image and text in the work of bill bissett</i></a> that analyses the poet's work.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4">I met with bill recently in Ottawa to talk about all of the above, starting with the blurring of boundaries. Please listen here:</span></p>]]></description>
