<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;">Ruth Panofsky is Professor of English at Ryerson University in Toronto where she specializes in Canadian Literature and Culture, focusing on Canadian authorship and publishing history. She is the author of <cite>The Force of Vocation: The Literary Career of Adele Wiseman</cite> and is currently preparing a SSHRC-funded history of the Macmillan Company of Canada, 1905-1986. We met this past summer in Toronto to talk about MacMillan, its history and some of the more important <a title="books" href="http://nigelbeale.com/2010/10/03/audio-interview-with-prof-ruth-panofsky-on-the-macmillan-company-of-canada/bookstores">books</a> and authors it has published. </span></p>
