			<title>McGill University Rare Book Librarian Richard Virr on Book Collecting</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://traffic.libsyn.com/nigelbeale/Richard_Virr_062908-104202.mp3]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><a title="Richard Virr by Nigel Beale, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nigelbeale/5046753905/"><img alt="Richard Virr" src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4117/5046753905_016a9f4449.jpg" width="278" height="369" /></a></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;" face="Times New Roman" size="4">Richard Virr is the Head and Curator of Manuscripts at the <a href="http://www.mcgill.ca/library/library-using/branches/rarebooks/">Rare Books and Special Collections Division of the McGill University Library.</a> We met recently in Montreal to talk about book collecting, characteristic traits of the book collector, and different kinds of collections, including the Stone and Kimball collection that was purchased by McGill in 1972. It holds most of the books published by Stone &amp; Kimball (1893-1897) of Cambridge, Chicago and New York, a publisher important primarily because of its focus on book quality and design. Please listen here:</span></p>]]></description>
            <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[51b7281a9ae0381d85e824e269db7250]]></guid>
            <media:thumbnail url="http://assets.libsyn.com/item/1197578" />
            <pubDate>Sun, 03 Oct 2010 09:34:00 +0000</pubDate>
			<itunes:keywords>and,stone,book,collecting,kimball,mcgill,librarian</itunes:keywords>

	<itunes:subtitle><![CDATA[
Richard Virr is the Head and Curator of Manuscripts at the Rare Books and Special Collections Division of the McGill University Library. We met recently in Montreal to talk about book collecting, characteristic traits of the book collector, and different kinds of collections, including the Stone and Kimball collection that was purchased by McGill in 1972. It holds most of the books published by Stone &amp; Kimball (1893-1897) of Cambridge, Chicago and New York, a publisher important primarily because of its focus on book quality and design. Please listen here:]]></itunes:subtitle>



