        <item>
			<title>Giller Prize Founder Jack Rabinovitch: On How to Pick the 'Best' Novels, and the merits of M.G. Vassanji</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://nigelbeale.libsyn.com/giller-prize-founder-jack-rabinovitch-on-how-to-pick-the-best-novels-and-the-merits-of-m-g-vassanji]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><a title="Jack Rabinovitch 011 by Nigel Beale, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nigelbeale/4957444375/"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4091/4957444375_75a4a8bdfe.jpg" alt="Jack Rabinovitch 011" width="285" height="414" /></a></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;"><strong>Jack Rabinovitch</strong> is a philanthropist best known for founding the annual <a title="Giller Prize" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giller_Prize" target="_blank">Scotia Bank Giller Prize</a> </span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;">(named after his late wife, Doris Giller, a former literary columnist and editor at the <em>Toronto Star)</em></span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;">for best Canadian novel. Rabinovitch, a reporter and speechwriter who later turned to business, making his fortune in food retailing and real estate,&nbsp; was an executive with <a title="Trizec Corporation (page does not exist)" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Trizec_Corporation&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" target="_blank">Trizec Corporation</a> where he helped develop close to six million square feet of hotel, commercial and retail space. He was <em><a title="Maclean's" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maclean%27s" target="_blank">Maclean&rsquo;s</a></em> magazine&rsquo;s man of the year in 1999 and is a recipient of the <a title="Order of Canada" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Order_of_Canada" target="_blank">Order of Canada</a> and the <a title="Order of Ontario" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Order_of_Ontario" target="_blank">Order of Ontario</a>.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;">This week his membership in the Order of Canada was upgraded to platinum&hellip;he is now an Officer of the Order. Part of the citation for this added honour reads:</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium;">"Jack Rabinovitch continues to lend extraordinary energy to the promotion of Canadian literature. Maintaining a very active leadership role in the administration of the Scotiabank Giller Prize, he has negotiated a partnership that has solidified the Giller as Canada&rsquo;s most lucrative and illustrious literary award. Canadian authors and publishers alike have gained increased sales as a direct result of either a nomination or a win, while the awards have helped to raise the profile of new and lesser-known authors."</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">We met this morning to talk about the Giller, its contribution to the purchase, reading and discussion of Canadian novels,&nbsp; the various strengths and weaknesses of literary juries&nbsp; adjudicating merit, and his choice for &lsquo;best&rsquo; Canadian novel of all time. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: x-small;"><a id="bodyLinks" href="http://nigelbeale.libsyn.com/rss" target="_blank"><strong>(Subscribe to Nigel Beale&rsquo;s </strong></a><strong><a href="http://nigelbeale.libsyn.com/rss" target="_blank"><strong>Biblio File Podcast here)</strong></a></strong></span></p>
<p>Copyright &copy; 2010 by Nigel Beale. www.nigelbeale.com</p>
