"New Directions was founded in 1936, when James Laughlin (1914 &ndash; 1997), then a twenty-two-year-old Harvard sophomore, issued the first of the New Directions anthologies. "I asked Ezra Pound for &lsquo;career advice,&rsquo;" James Laughlin recalled. "He had been seeing my poems for months and had ruled them hopeless. He urged me to finish Harvard and then do &rsquo;something&rsquo; useful." 

