            <media:thumbnail url="http://assets.libsyn.com/item/1197466" />
            <pubDate>Wed, 23 Sep 2009 00:13:00 +0000</pubDate>
			<itunes:keywords>books,john,first,book,morgan,library,collecting,jp,bidwell,hours,editions</itunes:keywords>

	<itunes:subtitle><![CDATA[
John Bid&shy;well is Astor Cur&shy;ator of Prin&shy;ted Books and Bind&shy;ings at thePier&shy;pont Mor&shy;gan Lib&shy;rary, before which he was Cur&shy;ator of Graphic Arts in the Prin&shy;ceton Uni&shy;ver&shy;sity Lib&shy;rary. He has writ&shy;ten extens&shy;ively on the his&shy;tory of paper&shy;mak&shy;ing in Eng&shy;land and America.&nbsp;
The Prin&shy;ted Books and Bind&shy;ings col&shy;lec&shy;tion at the Mor&shy;gan con&shy;tains works span&shy;ning West&shy;ern book pro&shy;duc&shy;tion from the earli&shy;est prin&shy;ted eph&shy;em&shy;era to import&shy;ant first edi&shy;tions from the twen&shy;ti&shy;eth cen&shy;tury. Hold&shy;ings encom&shy;pass a large num&shy;ber of high points in the his&shy;tory of print&shy;ing, often exem&shy;pli&shy;fied by a lone sur&shy;viv&shy;ing copy or a copy that is per&shy;fect in every way. Areas of strength include incun&shy;ables, early children&rsquo;s books, fine bind&shy;ings, and illus&shy;trated books.&nbsp;

Yolande de Sois&shy;sons in Prayer &ldquo;Psalter-Hours of Yolande de Sois&shy;sons&rdquo; France, Ami&shy;ens, ca. 1280&ndash;90 MS M.729, fol. 232v Pur&shy;chased by J. P. Mor&shy;gan, Jr.,&nbsp;1927
The col&shy;lec&shy;tion is foun&shy;ded upon acquis&shy;i&shy;tions of Pier&shy;pont Mor&shy;gan, who sought to estab&shy;lish in the United States a lib&shy;rary worthy of the great European col&shy;lec&shy;tions. Among the high&shy;lights are three Guten&shy;berg Bibles, works by Lord Byron, Charles Dick&shy;ens, Edgar Allan Poe, John Ruskin, Mark Twain, Her&shy;man Melville, and Wil&shy;liam Mor&shy;ris, and clas&shy;sic early children&rsquo;s books. The Carter Bur&shy;den Col&shy;lec&shy;tion of Amer&shy;ican Lit&shy;er&shy;at&shy;ure, a major 1998 gift, strengthens the Morgan&rsquo;s twentieth-century hold&shy;ings with authors such as Ted Hughes, Sylvia Plath, Vladi&shy;mir Nabokov, Ger&shy;trude Stein, and Ten&shy;nessee Williams.&nbsp;
I talk here with John Bid&shy;well about the col&shy;lec&shy;tion, what it con&shy;tains, how it was acquired.
&nbsp;Copy&shy;right &copy; 2009 by Nigel&nbsp;Beale.
