Terry Griggs is the author of a collection of short stories, Quickening, which was nominated for a Governor General&rsquo;s Award, and two novels, The Lusty Man, and Rogues&rsquo; Wedding, shortlisted for the Rogers Writers&rsquo; Trust Fiction Award. She has also written two books for children, Cat&rsquo;s Eye Corner, shortlisted for a Mr. Christie&rsquo;s Book Award and a Red Cedar Award, and most recently a sequel, The Silver Door. In 2003 she received the Marian Engel Award. Born on Manitoulin Island in Lake Huron, she currently lives in Stratford, Ontario.  
 
