	<itunes:subtitle><![CDATA[Born in Los Angeles in 1946, Robert Bringhurst is an award winning Canadian poet, typographer and author. Perhaps best known for &nbsp;The Elements of Typographic Style &ndash; a reference book of typefaces, glyphs and the visual and geometric arrangement of type, he is also a respected translator of poetic works from Haida into English. &nbsp;He lives on Quadra Island, near Campbell River, B.C. 
We met recently in Ottawa to talk about his definition of the book as articulated in The Surface of Meaning, and of typography and the services it ideally offers its readers, including:
Invite the reader into the text
