            <description><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><span><a href="http://www.sentex.net/%7Epql/metcalf.html"><span style="font-size: medium;">John Metcalf</span></a></span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: HELVETICA,ARIAL;" face="HELVETICA, ARIAL"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"> is best known as a writer/editor who has worked with many of Canada&rsquo;s foremost short story writers including</span></span></span><span style="font-family: HELVETICA,ARIAL;" face="HELVETICA, ARIAL"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Winter"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Michael Winter</span></span></a><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">, Terry Griggs, Steven Heighton, and Caroline Adderson. Born in Carlisle, England, and educated at the University of Bristol, he emigrated to Canada in 1962. In addition to writing his own novels, short stories and essays, he for years edited the work of others at the </span></span><a href="http://www.sentex.net/%7Epql/"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Porcupine&rsquo;s Quill</span></span></a><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">. He is currently Senior Editor with </span></span><a href="http://www.notesandqueries.ca/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=22&amp;Itemid=43"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Canadian Notes and Queries</span></span></a></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><span> magazine. Metcalf is also a serious book collector. <br /> </span></span></span></p>
