	<itunes:subtitle><![CDATA[
Rosemary Furtak has been librarian at the Walker Art Center in Minneapolis for 25 year. She is co-curator of &lsquo;Text Messages&rsquo;, an exhibit on artist&rsquo;s books currently showing (until April 2009) at the Center. We talk here about her early championing of the artist book genre (her definition being:&nbsp;"a book that refuses to behave like a book (like the 35,000 books that sit in the stacks"), the line between books and art, and words and art, and librarians and curators&hellip;and how to go about collecting artist books. We talk too about the challenges of cataloguing artist Ed Ruscha&rsquo;s 26 Gasoline Stations,

