			<title>Craig Poile co-owner of Collected Works on How to run a successful Independent Bookstore</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://traffic.libsyn.com/nigelbeale/Craig_Poile_Collected_Works.mp3]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2292/2282856258_a28d62fe09.jpg?v=0" vspace="0" width="283" align="bottom" border="0" height="211" hspace="0" /></p>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: small;" size="3">Listen here to my conversation with Craig Poile, co-owner of <a href="http://www.collected-works.com/">Collected Works</a>, a successful, innovative independent bookstore based in Ottawa, Canada. We talk, among others things, about a rudimentary webcam-teleconferencing system dubbed </span><span style="font-size: small;" size="3">&lsquo;Great Talking Head,&rsquo; that </span><span style="font-size: small;" size="3">Craig has set up to get big name authors, such as Julian Barnes and Peter Carey, and their fans, together in his bookstore; about bookseller-publisher relations, in-store writing workshops and print-on-demand. <br /></span></div>]]></description>
            <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[2f527881d12c3bccd4368635dd406f53]]></guid>
