We look at the author as brand, the feigned disinterest many authors hold for the business side of publishing books, Harlan&rsquo;s New York Times Op-Ed pieces, his preference for the missing over the dead, suburban desperation, and 2.5 million books sold worldwide each year. &nbsp;
