			<title>Author Illustrator Barbara Reid on Illustrating Children's Books</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://nigelbeale.libsyn.com/author-illustrator-barbara-reid]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Barbara Reid&rsquo;s Plasticine artwork makes her books instantly recognizable. They have won acclaim around the world, and many awards. We talk here about what makes her so good, about great children&rsquo;s book illustrators, the accurate conveyance of emotion, mice in subways, making room for the imagination, chiaroscuro, working in ice cream, wanting to show things to those you love, pony tails, playing hooky and war.</span></p>
