			<title>Johnathon Green on Slang</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://traffic.libsyn.com/nigelbeale/Johnathon_Green_Slang_Interview.mp3]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://farm1.static.flickr.com/94/214256764_f7c16ee76f.jpg?v=0" height="347" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="260" align="bottom" border="0" /></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: small;" size="3">Why Penises Beat Out Vaginas</span></strong></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;" size="3">Rap as rebellion, slang as hipness, and jargon as obfuscatory exclusionary pretense, these are topics discussed during an interview with world-leading slang lexicographer Jonathon Green last month in his office in London, England. And bloody invigorating it was too. We talk about why penises are funny and beat out vaginas, why slang is negative and misogynist and how it carries a kind of inventive cleverness seldom found in the harmless drudgery of every day language, Samuel Johnson&rsquo;s political bias, Eric Partridge&rsquo;s connection with my relative Paul Beale, Jonathon&rsquo;s insistence on austere objectivity, and the fact that he simply can&rsquo;t afford to piss around having fun. Copyright &copy; 2006 by Nigel Beale.</span></p>]]></description>
            <guid isPermaLink="false"><![CDATA[f387171cfddd9604fc664c6a5ec048d8]]></guid>
            <media:thumbnail url="http://assets.libsyn.com/item/1196935" />
            <pubDate>Wed, 12 Apr 2006 01:51:00 +0000</pubDate>
			<itunes:keywords>jargon,sex,rap,slang,dictionaries</itunes:keywords>

	<itunes:subtitle><![CDATA[
Why Penises Beat Out Vaginas
Rap as rebellion, slang as hipness, and jargon as obfuscatory exclusionary pretense, these are topics discussed during an interview with world-leading slang lexicographer Jonathon Green last month in his office in London, England. And bloody invigorating it was too. We talk about why penises are funny and beat out vaginas, why slang is negative and misogynist and how it carries a kind of inventive cleverness seldom found in the harmless drudgery of every day language, Samuel Johnson&rsquo;s political bias, Eric Partridge&rsquo;s connection with my relative Paul Beale, Jonathon&rsquo;s insistence on austere objectivity, and the fact that he simply can&rsquo;t afford to piss around having fun. Copyright &copy; 2006 by Nigel Beale.]]></itunes:subtitle>



